observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor and all other Municipal officials and employees strictly comply with the requirements and mechanics prescribed under Presidential EO No. 77 in their claims for reimbursement for official travels. Specifically:
Claims for official local travels of the Municipal Mayor be supported with duly approved travel orders/authorities to travel issued by the Provincial Governor, Certificates of Appearance and Certificates of Travel Completed;
All claims for official travel should not exceed the rates authorized under Presidential EO No. 77;
Accommodation claims in excess of the accommodation component of the DTE, but not to exceed 100% of such component, be supported with a certification by the Head of the Agency that those expenses were absolutely necessary in the performance of their assignments; and
Other expenses of the Municipal Mayor other than travelling expenses, during the duration of the travel, be charged to other line-item expense budgets, subject to availability of funds and the limits set in Section 325 (h) of RA No. 7160.

We reiterated our recommendation that:
The Inventory Committee complete its inventory taking on all LGU properties and prepare a report thereof;
Duly accomplish the Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) of all unserviceable PPE;
Submit to the Municipal Accountant as basis for derecognizing from the books the aforementioned PPEs to ensure the correctness of the PPE account reflected in the financial statements; and
Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare the Journal Entry Voucher to derecognize the properties.

