We recommended the following:
For every procurement, the BAC thru the BAC secretariat, attach the evidence of invitation of three observers in all stages of the procurement process and the printout copy of posting of Notice of Award, Notice to Proceed and Contract of Award in the PhilGEPS, the website of the Procuring Entity, if any, and any conspicuous place in the premises of the Procuring Entity as supporting documents in the payment of infrastructure projects;
The Municipal Engineer should accomplish the Statement of Time Elapsed and Work Accomplished;
The Statement of Work Accomplished prepared by the contractor should be inspected and verified by the Project Engineer, Municipal Engineer and MPDC;
The LGU create an inspectorate team that will verify the accomplishment of the contractor per Statement of Work Accomplished and prepare the Inspection Report for the final payment of the 100% accomplishment of work.
Submit the required supporting documents enumerated above.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the ICO, Municipal Treasurer to effectively collect business taxes from Semirara Mining and Power Corporation annually through:

Obtain a copy of the published Statement of Financial Performance from Securities and Exchange Commission and the Bureau of Internal Revenue or download from their website for the correct assessment


of business tax;

Issue the correct billing statement based on the published Statement of Financial Performance periodically;

Request the assistance from the Provincial Legal Officer or Prosecutor in accordance with Sections 481 and 31 of RA 7160, if necessary.
